{"type":"message","id":"65d3206e","parentId":"422b4a1a","timestamp":"2026-04-12T00:45:53.840Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me check the full .env file to see what's there.","thinkingSignature":"9aacb3cb61fcb7691f027a36014d1e92116f330004e364d260cf7fa002fe04ed"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_n4x9czh7ep5h_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /home/travis/Lookitry/openclaw/.env 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":83,"output":55,"cacheRead":29440,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":29578,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775954752631,"responseId":"062a1e402609200bd3483b0be417d2d3"}}
{"type":"message","id":"a2598764","parentId":"65d3206e","timestamp":"2026-04-12T00:45:53.877Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_n4x9czh7ep5h_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# OpenClaw .env example\n#\n# Quick start:\n# 1) Copy this file to `.env` (for local runs from this repo), OR to `~/.openclaw/.env` (for launchd/systemd daemons).\n# 2) Fill only the values you use.\n# 3) Keep real secrets out of git.\n#\n# Env-source precedence for environment variables (highest -> lowest):\n# process env, ./.env, ~/.openclaw/.env, then openclaw.json `env` block.\n# Existing non-empty process env vars are not overridden by dotenv/config env loading.\n# Note: direct config keys (for example `gateway.auth.token` or channel tokens in openclaw.json)\n# are resolved separately from env loading and often take precedence over env fallbacks.\n\n# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Gateway auth + paths\n# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Recommended if the gateway binds beyond loopback.\nOPENCLAW_GATEWAY_TOKEN=change-me-to-a-long-random-token\n# Example generator: openssl rand -hex 32\n\n# Optional alternative auth mode (use token OR password).\n# OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_PASSWORD=change-me-to-a-strong-password\n\n# Optional path overrides (defaults shown for reference).\n# OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR=~/.openclaw\n# OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH=~/.openclaw/openclaw.json\n# OPENCLAW_HOME=~\n\n# Optional: import missing keys from your login shell profile.\n# OPENCLAW_LOAD_SHELL_ENV=1\n# OPENCLAW_SHELL_ENV_TIMEOUT_MS=15000\n\n# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Model provider API keys (set at least one)\n# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...\n# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...\n# GEMINI_API_KEY=...\n# OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-...\n# OPENCLAW_LIVE_OPENAI_KEY=sk-...\n# OPENCLAW_LIVE_ANTHROPIC_KEY=sk-ant-...\n# OPENCLAW_LIVE_GEMINI_KEY=...\n# OPENAI_API_KEY_1=...\n# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY_1=...\n# GEMINI_API_KEY_1=...\n# GOOGLE_API_KEY=...\n# OPENAI_API_KEYS=sk-1,sk-2\n# ANTHROPIC_API_KEYS=sk-ant-1,sk-ant-2\n# GEMINI_API_KEYS=key-1,key-2\n\n# Optional additional providers\n# ZAI_API_KEY=...\n# AI_GATEWAY_API_KEY=...\n# MINIMAX_API_KEY=...\n# SYNTHETIC_API_KEY=...\n\n# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Channels (only set what you enable)\n# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=123456:ABCDEF...\n# DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN=...\n# SLACK_BOT_TOKEN=xoxb-...\n# SLACK_APP_TOKEN=xapp-...\n\n# Optional channel env fallbacks\n# MATTERMOST_BOT_TOKEN=...\n# MATTERMOST_URL=https://chat.example.com\n# ZALO_BOT_TOKEN=...\n# OPENCLAW_TWITCH_ACCESS_TOKEN=oauth:...\n\n# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Tools + voice/media (optional)\n# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# BRAVE_API_KEY=...\n# PERPLEXITY_API_KEY=pplx-...\n# FIRECRAWL_API_KEY=...\n\n# ELEVENLABS_API_KEY=...\n# XI_API_KEY=...  # alias for ElevenLabs\n# DEEPGRAM_API_KEY=..."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":24,"aggregated":"# OpenClaw .env example\n#\n# Quick start:\n# 1) Copy this file to `.env` (for local runs from this repo), OR to `~/.openclaw/.env` (for launchd/systemd daemons).\n# 2) Fill only the values you use.\n# 3) Keep real secrets out of git.\n#\n# Env-source precedence for environment variables (highest -> lowest):\n# process env, ./.env, ~/.openclaw/.env, then openclaw.json `env` block.\n# Existing non-empty process env vars are not overridden by dotenv/config env loading.\n# Note: direct config keys (for example `gateway.auth.token` or channel tokens in openclaw.json)\n# are resolved separately from env loading and often take precedence over env fallbacks.\n\n# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Gateway auth + paths\n# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Recommended if the gateway binds beyond loopback.\nOPENCLAW_GATEWAY_TOKEN=change-me-to-a-long-random-token\n# Example generator: openssl rand -hex 32\n\n# Optional alternative auth mode (use token OR password).\n# OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_PASSWORD=change-me-to-a-strong-password\n\n# Optional path overrides (defaults shown for reference).\n# OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR=~/.openclaw\n# OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH=~/.openclaw/openclaw.json\n# OPENCLAW_HOME=~\n\n# Optional: import missing keys from your login shell profile.\n# OPENCLAW_LOAD_SHELL_ENV=1\n# OPENCLAW_SHELL_ENV_TIMEOUT_MS=15000\n\n# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Model provider API keys (set at least one)\n# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...\n# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...\n# GEMINI_API_KEY=...\n# OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-...\n# OPENCLAW_LIVE_OPENAI_KEY=sk-...\n# OPENCLAW_LIVE_ANTHROPIC_KEY=sk-ant-...\n# OPENCLAW_LIVE_GEMINI_KEY=...\n# OPENAI_API_KEY_1=...\n# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY_1=...\n# GEMINI_API_KEY_1=...\n# GOOGLE_API_KEY=...\n# OPENAI_API_KEYS=sk-1,sk-2\n# ANTHROPIC_API_KEYS=sk-ant-1,sk-ant-2\n# GEMINI_API_KEYS=key-1,key-2\n\n# Optional additional providers\n# ZAI_API_KEY=...\n# AI_GATEWAY_API_KEY=...\n# MINIMAX_API_KEY=...\n# SYNTHETIC_API_KEY=...\n\n# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Channels (only set what you enable)\n# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=123456:ABCDEF...\n# DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN=...\n# SLACK_BOT_TOKEN=xoxb-...\n# SLACK_APP_TOKEN=xapp-...\n\n# Optional channel env fallbacks\n# MATTERMOST_BOT_TOKEN=...\n# MATTERMOST_URL=https://chat.example.com\n# ZALO_BOT_TOKEN=...\n# OPENCLAW_TWITCH_ACCESS_TOKEN=oauth:...\n\n# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Tools + voice/media (optional)\n# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# BRAVE_API_KEY=...\n# PERPLEXITY_API_KEY=pplx-...\n# FIRECRAWL_API_KEY=...\n\n# ELEVENLABS_API_KEY=...\n# XI_API_KEY=...  # alias for ElevenLabs\n# DEEPGRAM_API_KEY=...","cwd":"/home/travis/Lookitry/Lookitry/sammy"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775954753873}}
{"type":"message","id":"b324044d","parentId":"a2598764","timestamp":"2026-04-12T00:45:58.204Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `.env` file is just a template/example, no actual keys are there. Wilkie said the OpenCode API key is on the Hostinger VPS in the `.env` file there. So I need to access the Hostinger VPS to get the key.\n\nWait, but I'm running as the local OpenClaw on this machine. How would I access the Hostinger VPS? I could SSH to it if they have the connection details.\n\nLet me think... Wilkie is working on the Hostinger VPS. Maybe they have SSH access configured. Let me check if there's an SSH config or if I can access the VPS.\n\nActually wait - I'm running on the same machine where OpenClaw is installed (`/home/travis/Lookitry/openclaw`). The `.env` I just read is the local one. \n\nThe OpenCode key might actually be stored on the Hostinger VPS itself, or possibly already configured in the openclaw.json on that remote machine. Since they're away from the VPS right now, they might just be asking me to help them set it up locally instead.\n\nActually, thinking about this more carefully - they said \"you can get it there\" about the Hostinger VPS, which suggests they expected me to access it remotely. But I'm running locally on their machine, so I can't directly reach the VPS. I could try asking for SSH credentials to connect, or they might have a way to share the key directly with me.","thinkingSignature":"89c5598e9004dd001d098b1ca99eb9beb17874e1a87b383103f420dc07c3dfb5"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nNo veo la key de OpenCode en el `.env` local (solo es un template de ejemplo). \n\n¿Tienes las credenciales SSH del VPS de Hostinger para que pueda acceder y buscar la key? O si la key ya está configurada en el `openclaw.json` del VPS, puedo ayudarte a activarla desde ahí.\n\n¿Cómo quieres proceed?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":788,"output":368,"cacheRea