{"type":"message","id":"d76103ee","parentId":"744a9f49","timestamp":"2026-04-12T01:09:00.448Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the issue - the `webhook_secret` has a default value that's hardcoded. The user needs this to work with their n8n setup. I should:\n\n1. Change the default to a placeholder that makes it clear it needs to be replaced, OR\n2. Use an environment variable reference\n\nBut wait - if I change the default, it might break the n8n integration that's already using this secret. The user needs to update their n8n webhook configuration with a new secret.\n\nLet me think about the best approach:\n1. The schema has a hardcoded default - this is bad practice\n2. The actual secret being used is 'Travis2305**_blog_n8n'\n\n\n3. For production, this should come from an environment variable\n\nThe safest fix that won't break anything is to generate a proper placeholder that signals this needs to be replaced in production, rather than removing it entirely or using a real secret. I need to handle this delicately since it could break the n8n setup if I remove the default without providing a replacement value.\n\nMy approach is to replace the hardcoded secret with a placeholder that makes it clear an environment variable should be used instead, so I'll check how other secrets are structured in the schema and then update this one accordingly.","thinkingSignature":"f3d98dcc2ff827e162af0af76b0cd08f952dd83b9b7f4f1de80540268615d557"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rl51rrpu63go_1","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":15,"offset":70,"path":"/home/travis/Lookitry/Lookitry/backend/supabase-schema.sql"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":281,"output":321,"cacheRead":57408,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":58010,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775956132149,"responseId":"062a23a4843d8ae670308b9ee81e68a2"