{"type":"message","id":"ad124c97","parentId":"2aee044a","timestamp":"2026-04-12T01:58:12.388Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There are two issues:\n1. The middleware has an issue with the prerender-manifest\n2. The Tailwind CSS isn't being processed properly (globals.css is showing raw content)\n\nThe problem is that the `mission-control.css` file is using `@tailwind` directives but it's a plain CSS file, not a PostCSS-processed file. In Next.js, the CSS files in `src/app/` are not processed by Tailwind automatically unless they're imported in a specific way.\n\nAlso, there seems to be an issue with the middleware. Let me check the middleware file.\n","thinkingSignature":"caa835793ca385435d67cd99779e85eb48f34652eec56b4eded2d316829f8232"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\nHay dos problemas:\n\n1. **El CSS de Tailwind no se está procesando** - el archivo `mission-control.css` tiene directivas `@tailwind` pero Next.js no lo está procesando correctamente\n2. **Error en el middleware** con `prerender-manifest.js`\n\nVoy a arreglarlo:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8nt3jz4rxh9o_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"head -30 /home/travis/Lookitry/Lookitry/frontend/src/app/mission-control/mission-control.css 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":69,"output":233,"cacheRead":106784,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":107086,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775959086365,"responseId":"062a2f2e478ae0d9f6ffb637626888f8"}}
