{"type":"message","id":"7f8b3f53","parentId":"17e776c4","timestamp":"2026-04-12T01:58:32.732Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to fix the Tailwind issue. The problem is that `mission-control.css` uses `@tailwind` directives, but it's being processed as a CSS module, which doesn't work with Tailwind. \n\nThe solution is to keep the Tailwind directives in `globals.css` or a separate non-module CSS file, and only use CSS module for the custom mission control styles.\n\nLet me check if there's a way to fix this. Actually, the issue is that the page is importing `mission-control.css` which has `@tailwind` directives, but as a CSS module import it won't work.\n\nThe proper solution: \n1. Keep `@tailwind` directives in the regular CSS files (globals.css)\n2. Move mission-control custom styles to a `.module.css` file (which I already did by renaming)\n\n\n3. Make sure `globals.css` is imported in layout.tsx (which it should be already)\n\nLooking at the page.tsx, it's importing the CSS file with `@tailwind` directives as a CSS module, which is the core issue. I need to check if globals.css already has these directives or if I need to move them there instead.","thinkingSignature":"97fab9ab0d2d45ee2b198784f3ac12073c627da54ac23f59b852a34ad0f7cb8a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_aq43evhhg9ha_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"head -10 /home/travis/Lookitry/Lookitry/frontend/src/app/globals.css 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":156,"output":283,"cacheRead":107488,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":107927,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775959105057,"responseId":"062a2f4168b9b5de1bb9391b4aef5f97"}}
