{"type":"message","id":"2638d7e8","parentId":"6d1b5999","timestamp":"2026-04-12T02:23:46.857Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants Rebecca to be able to talk to Sammy and have access to project information. This means they want to set up communication between Rebecca and me, or give Rebecca access to the project context.\n\nLooking at the OpenClaw setup, Rebecca is defined as an agent in openclaw.json with her own workspace. The user probably wants:\n1. Rebecca to be able to collaborate with Sammy\n2. Rebecca to have access to project information (Lookitry project)\n\nThere are a few ways to handle this:\n1. Rebecca can be spawned as a subagent to work on tasks\n2. Rebecca's workspace could be set up with proper context\n3. Rebecca could be added to the same Telegram group/channel so she can communicate\n\n\n4. Or they might be asking me to share project information directly with Rebecca through a message\n\nI should clarify what they're looking for—whether they want Rebecca spawned as a subagent for a specific task, or if they're asking me to send project context to Rebecca's workspace so she has the information readily available.","thinkingSignature":"03e6099911a33d6287002650c86aa4145bbd6fc6666756ac8d74014bd526cbce"},{"type":"text","text":"Entiendo — quieres que Rebecca tenga acceso al proyecto y pueda comunicarse conmigo.\n\nHay dos partes:\n\n### 1. **Rebecca recibe info del proyecto**\nNecesito agregar el proyecto Lookitry a su workspace. Actualmente su workspace está vacío:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7uz07pr8a3zz_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la /home/travis/.openclaw/workspaces/rebecca/ 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":92,"output":303,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":125346,"totalTokens":125741,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775960611895,"responseI