{"type":"message","id":"69d90f33","parentId":"13cebae4","timestamp":"2026-04-12T02:24:04.030Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Rebecca has a workspace with AGENTS.md, SOUL.md, etc. but doesn't have access to the Lookitry project files. \n\nThe user wants Rebecca to be able to:\n1. Talk to Sammy (me)\n2. Have access to project information\n\nTo give Rebecca access to the Lookitry project, I could:\n1. Create a symlink to the Lookitry project in Rebecca's workspace\n2. Or add project files to her workspace\n\nLet me create a symlink or reference to the Lookitry project in her workspace, and also set up a way for her to communicate with me.\n\nActually, looking at the openclaw.json config, Rebecca is defined as an agent with her own workspace. For her to collaborate with me, we'd need to either:\n1. Have her spawned as a subagent when needed\n2. Use sessions_send to send messages between us\n3. Set up a shared memory/context\n\nLet me create a symlink to the Lookitry project in her workspace and also add a reference file that points to the project.","thinkingSignature":"da3c6c1aeb5aa537c88e76d1511d6f58e1a0861e4f0de4a2040d0332869d2a48"},{"type":"text","text":"Rebecca ya tiene su workspace configurado pero no tiene acceso al proyecto Lookitry. Voy a:\n1. Agregar referencia al proyecto en su workspace\n2. Configurar un canal de comunicación entre ella y yo\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rasqywhwkoca_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ln -sf /home/travis/Lookitry/Lookitry /home/travis/.openclaw/workspaces/rebecca/Lookitry 2>&1 && ls -la /home/travis/.openclaw/workspaces/rebecca/"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":113511,"output":341,"cacheRead":14507,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":128359,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775960632618,"responseId":"062a3539d09b882fd4b4e58356d2ea4d"}}
